<br>
well, there's lots of ways of getting pen pals.  If you even just go online and do a search on &quot;japanese pen pals&quot; you'll find a ton of sites in short order (well, after you weed out the ones which are actually fronts for psuedo-mail order brides LOL).  If you wanna do it the digital way, i would even recommend looking on the ICQ chat rooms (you'll have to go through the ICQ site)  as there's a bunch of japanese people who are looking for english speaking pen pals/ want to do language/culture exchange, just wanna make friends, etc.  If you happen to be in japan, you can always pick up a copy of Tokyo Classified (now called metropolis i think, i know they have a web site, which may or may not have the appropriate links) which has tons and tons of ads for people looking for pen pals (among other things- hilarious reading  ).  Otherwise, if you live in a big city, they might have some sort of japanese community organization, they no doubt could hook you up.<br>
<br>
Finally, and one of the best ways, in my opinion, is to be a conversation partner.  Usually most medium-large cities will have an ESL school (like a language academy) which will teach foreigners english, it's kind of a matter of luck, but sometimes (like the one in my city) there will be tons of japanese students.  These schools generally love it if native english speakers volunteer to be language exchange partners, and the really cool part is, you get to have face to face interaction and have the opportunity to learn so much more not only about language but culture etc. than just from a class/web site/pen pal letter.  Plus you can meet many interesting people and make great friends!  (LOL I sound like an advertisment!)  <br>
<br>
Anyway, like i said, the last part kind of depends on luck, and where you live as to whether or not you'll have many japanese students at that school.  But IMHO if that option is open to you, you should take it!  Plus who knows- maybe you'll meet a cute girl <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->    (or guy for you gals on the board!)<br>
<br>
Anyway, i hope that helps.  If you need more details about any of that stuff (icq chat room address, etc.) let me know! <p><B> <I>Ask me about microwaving cats for fun and profit! </I> </B><BR>
